com.siperian.sif.message.mrm

Class GetDependentObjectRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianRequest
      • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianObjectRequest
        • com.siperian.sif.message.mrm.GetDependentObjectRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RecordKeyProvider, SiperianObjectUidProvider, Serializable
    Deprecated. 
    As of 9.0

    public class GetDependentObjectRequest
extends SiperianObjectRequest
implements RecordKeyProvider
    Retrieves a dependent object record for the dependent source key and record key specified. The record key identifies the parent base object record, and the dependent source key identifies the child dependent object record.

    Required Parameters:

    • setRecordKey(RecordKey) - RecordKey object representing the key of the parent base object record.
    • setDependentSourceKey(String) - Source key of the dependent object record
    • SiperianObjectRequest.setSiperianObjectUid(String) - the dependent object.

    Usage Example:

    The following example retrieves a dependent object record with source key 100 that is a child of the base object record with ROWID_OBJECT key 782 in the CUSTOMER_NOTE package. It is assumed that this package is based on the dependent object of NOTE that is a child of the CUSTOMER base object.

    GetDependentObjectRequest request = new GetDependentObjectRequest();
    request.setSiperianObjectUid("PACKAGE.CUSTOMER_NOTE");
    RecordKey recordKey = new RecordKey();
    recordKey.setRowid("782");
    recordKey.setSystemName("SALES");
    request.setRecordKey(recordKey);
    request.setDependentSourceKey("100");
    //process the request
    GetDependentObjectResponse response =
    (GetDependentObjectResponse) sipClient.process(request);

    See Also:
    GetDependentObjectResponse, RecordKey, GetRequest, Serialized Form

    API Pair: GetDependentObjectResponse

    API Group: Data Retrieval
